#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:3
msgid "Algorithms"
msgstr "演算法"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:5
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:8
msgid "What's Included"
msgstr "包含哪些內容"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:10
msgid "The following algorithms are implemented in the Spinning Up package:"
msgstr "Spinning Up 套件中實作了以下演算法："

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:12
msgid "`Vanilla Policy Gradient`_ (VPG)"
msgstr "`Vanilla Policy Gradient`_ (VPG, 基本策略梯度)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:13
msgid "`Trust Region Policy Optimization`_ (TRPO)"
msgstr "`Trust Region Policy Optimization`_ (TRPO, 信賴域策略最佳化)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:14
msgid "`Proximal Policy Optimization`_ (PPO)"
msgstr "`Proximal Policy Optimization`_ (PPO, 近端策略最佳化)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:15
msgid "`Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient`_ (DDPG)"
msgstr "`Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient`_ (DDPG, 深度確定性策略梯度)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:16
msgid "`Twin Delayed DDPG`_ (TD3)"
msgstr "`Twin Delayed DDPG`_ (TD3, 雙延遲 DDPG)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:17
msgid "`Soft Actor-Critic`_ (SAC)"
msgstr "`Soft Actor-Critic`_ (SAC, 軟演員-評論家)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:19
msgid ""
"They are all implemented with `MLP`_ (non-recurrent) actor-critics, "
"making them suitable for fully-observed, non-image-based RL environments,"
" e.g. the `Gym Mujoco`_ environments."
msgstr ""
"這些演算法都使用 `MLP`_（多層感知器，非遞迴）的演員-評論家 (actor-critic) 架構實作，"
"適用於完全可觀測、非影像的強化學習 (Reinforcement Learning, RL) 環境，"
"例如 `Gym Mujoco`_ 環境。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:21
msgid ""
"Spinning Up has two implementations for each algorithm (except for TRPO):"
" one that uses `PyTorch`_ as the neural network library, and one that "
"uses `Tensorflow v1`_ as the neural network library. (TRPO is currently "
"only available in Tensorflow.)"
msgstr ""
"Spinning Up 為每個演算法（TRPO 除外）提供了兩種實作版本："
"一種使用 `PyTorch`_ 作為神經網路函式庫，另一種使用 `Tensorflow v1`_ 作為神經網路函式庫。"
"（TRPO 目前僅有 Tensorflow 版本。）"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:36
msgid "Why These Algorithms?"
msgstr "為什麼選擇這些演算法？"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:38
msgid ""
"We chose the core deep RL algorithms in this package to reflect useful "
"progressions of ideas from the recent history of the field, culminating "
"in two algorithms in particular---PPO and SAC---which are close to state "
"of the art on reliability and sample efficiency among policy-learning "
"algorithms. They also expose some of the trade-offs that get made in "
"designing and using algorithms in deep RL."
msgstr ""
"我們選擇這些核心深度 RL 演算法，是為了展現該領域近年來有用的思想演進，"
"最終聚焦於兩個演算法——PPO 和 SAC——它們在策略學習 (policy learning) 演算法中，"
"於可靠性和樣本效率 (sample efficiency) 方面接近最先進水準。"
"這些演算法也揭示了深度 RL 演算法設計與使用中的一些取捨。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:41
msgid "The On-Policy Algorithms"
msgstr "同策略演算法 (On-Policy Algorithms)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:43
msgid ""
"Vanilla Policy Gradient is the most basic, entry-level algorithm in the "
"deep RL space because it completely predates the advent of deep RL "
"altogether. The core elements of VPG go all the way back to the late 80s "
"/ early 90s. It started a trail of research which ultimately led to "
"stronger algorithms such as TRPO and then PPO soon after."
msgstr ""
"基本策略梯度 (Vanilla Policy Gradient) 是深度 RL 領域中最基礎的入門演算法，"
"因為它完全早於深度 RL 的出現。VPG 的核心要素可以追溯到 1980 年代末 / 1990 年代初。"
"它開啟了一系列研究，最終催生出更強大的演算法，如 TRPO，隨後不久又有了 PPO。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:45
msgid ""
"A key feature of this line of work is that all of these algorithms are "
"*on-policy*: that is, they don't use old data, which makes them weaker on"
" sample efficiency. But this is for a good reason: these algorithms "
"directly optimize the objective you care about---policy performance---and"
" it works out mathematically that you need on-policy data to calculate "
"the updates. So, this family of algorithms trades off sample efficiency "
"in favor of stability---but you can see the progression of techniques "
"(from VPG to TRPO to PPO) working to make up the deficit on sample "
"efficiency."
msgstr ""
"這一系列工作的關鍵特點是，所有這些演算法都是*同策略 (on-policy)* 的："
"也就是說，它們不使用舊資料，這使得樣本效率較低。"
"但這是有充分理由的：這些演算法直接最佳化你關心的目標——策略效能 (policy performance)——"
"而從數學上來說，你需要同策略資料才能計算更新。"
"因此，這一類演算法以犧牲樣本效率來換取穩定性——"
"但你可以看到技術的演進（從 VPG 到 TRPO 再到 PPO）正在努力彌補樣本效率上的不足。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:49
msgid "The Off-Policy Algorithms"
msgstr "離策略演算法 (Off-Policy Algorithms)"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:51
msgid ""
"DDPG is a similarly foundational algorithm to VPG, although much younger"
"---the theory of deterministic policy gradients, which led to DDPG, "
"wasn't published until 2014. DDPG is closely connected to Q-learning "
"algorithms, and it concurrently learns a Q-function and a policy which "
"are updated to improve each other."
msgstr ""
"DDPG 是與 VPG 同樣具有奠基意義的演算法，但要年輕得多——"
"催生 DDPG 的確定性策略梯度 (deterministic policy gradient) 理論直到 2014 年才發表。"
"DDPG 與 Q 學習 (Q-learning) 演算法密切相關，"
"它同時學習一個 Q 函數 (Q-function) 和一個策略 (policy)，兩者透過互相更新來共同改善。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:53
msgid ""
"Algorithms like DDPG and Q-Learning are *off-policy*, so they are able to"
" reuse old data very efficiently. They gain this benefit by exploiting "
"Bellman's equations for optimality, which a Q-function can be trained to "
"satisfy using *any* environment interaction data (as long as there's "
"enough experience from the high-reward areas in the environment)."
msgstr ""
"像 DDPG 和 Q-Learning 這類演算法是*離策略 (off-policy)* 的，因此能夠非常高效地重複使用舊資料。"
"它們透過利用 Bellman 最優方程式來獲得這一優勢，"
"Q 函數可以使用*任何*環境互動資料進行訓練（只要有足夠來自環境中高獎勵區域的經驗）。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:55
msgid ""
"But problematically, there are no guarantees that doing a good job of "
"satisfying Bellman's equations leads to having great policy performance. "
"*Empirically* one can get great performance---and when it happens, the "
"sample efficiency is wonderful---but the absence of guarantees makes "
"algorithms in this class potentially brittle and unstable. TD3 and SAC "
"are descendants of DDPG which make use of a variety of insights to "
"mitigate these issues."
msgstr ""
"但問題在於，沒有任何保證能證明良好地滿足 Bellman 方程式就能帶來出色的策略效能。"
"*從經驗上*來看確實可以獲得很好的效能——而且一旦成功，樣本效率非常出色——"
"但缺乏保證使得這類演算法可能脆弱且不穩定。"
"TD3 和 SAC 是 DDPG 的後繼演算法，運用了多種見解來緩解這些問題。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:59
msgid "Code Format"
msgstr "程式碼格式"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:61
msgid ""
"All implementations in Spinning Up adhere to a standard template. They "
"are split into two files: an algorithm file, which contains the core "
"logic of the algorithm, and a core file, which contains various utilities"
" needed to run the algorithm."
msgstr ""
"Spinning Up 中的所有實作都遵循一個標準範本。"
"它們被分成兩個檔案：一個演算法檔案，包含演算法的核心邏輯；"
"一個核心檔案，包含執行演算法所需的各種工具函式。"

#: ../../user/algorithms.rst:63
msgid ""
"The algorithm file always starts with a class definition for an "
"experience buffer object, which is used to store information from agent-"
"environment interactions. Next, there is a single function which runs the"
" algorithm. The algorithm function follows a template that is roughly the"
" same across the PyTorch and Tensorflow versions, but we'll break it down"
" for each separately below. Finally, there's some support in each "
"algorithm file for directly running the algorithm in Gym environments "
"from the command line (though this is not the recommended way to run the "
"algorithms---we'll describe how to do that on the `Running Experiments`_ "
"page)."
msgstr ""
"演算法檔案總是以一個經驗緩衝區 (experience buffer) 物件的類別定義開始，"
"用於儲存代理 (agent) 與環境互動的資訊。"
"接著是一個執行演算法的函式。演算法函式遵循的範本在 PyTorch 和 Tensorflow 版本中大致相同，"
"但我們會在下方分別說明。最後，每個演算法檔案都支援從命令列直接在 Gym 環境中執行演算法"
"（但這不是推薦的執行方式——我們將在 `Running Experiments`_ 頁面說明推薦的做法）。"

